defaultSchool autonomy is a good thing if it is within a system that allows cooperation and support for weak schools.  School autonomy 
defaultalso needs to exist within a system of strong, external accountability.  If autonomy leads to a free for all, then the school system 
defaultfragment, the difference in outcomes between schools grows
default and standards fall overall.’
default              default(defaultAndreas Schleicher, Head of 
defaultEducation Analysis for the OECD, in a report published on 13 September 2011, ‘Education at a Glance’)
