defaultQdefaultuestion 7defaultWhat alternatives to sponsored academy status should be offered to failing primary schools default&#xa0;default7.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn some cases, where radical improvement and re-organisation are needed to respond to a history of failure and under-performance an academy sponsor solution
default is appropriate, where it will bring significant additional capacity for improvement. KCC supports these solutions and values the opportunity to work with sponsors to bring these structural solutions to fruition, and have an on-going working relationship. 
default&#xa0;
default7.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn other cases however, we have been able to broker a quicker solution for improvement by developing a hard federation with an outstanding local school or by brokering a soft federation, established through the Kent School Collaborative Partnerships who kn
defaultow each other’s capabilities and trust each other. In these cases we seek stronger and sometimes new school leadership and more effective governance, which often achieves a very quick turnaround and 
defaulta 
defaultsustainable upward trend in a school’s performance.  
default&#xa0;
default7.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultKCC prefers a more mixed approach with some flexibility. Often it seems the D
defaultf
defaultE is only inte
defaultrested in one kind of solution.
